title: Doug Emhoff
added: == Second Gentleman of the United States ==

Following the election of [[Joe Biden]] as the 46th President of the United States in November 2020, Emhoff is expected to become the first Second Gentleman of the United States in January 2021 as he is the spouse of [[President-elect of the United States|Vice President-elect]] [[Kamala Harris]].

title: Doug Emhoff
deleted: Harris was announced as [[Joe Biden]]'s running mate for the [[2020 United States presidential election]] on August 11, 2020, meaning Emhoff is the third man in US history to be the spouse of a vice presidential running mate of a major political party, following [[John Zaccaro]] and [[Todd Palin]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Emmrich|first=Stuart|date=August 13, 2020|title=The 9 Things We Know About Kamala Harrisâ€™s Husband|work=[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]]|url=https://www.vogue.com/article/nine-things-we-know-about-kamala-harris-husband-douglas-emhoff|accessdate=15 August 2020}}</ref> With Harris' election, Emhoff is slated to become the first [[Second Spouse of the United States|second gentleman of the United States]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Edelman|first=Adam|date=August 13, 2020|title=The first 'second gentleman'? Meet Kamala Harris' husband, Doug Emhoff|work=[[NBC News]]|url=https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2020-election/first-second-gentleman-meet-kamala-harris-husband-doug-emhoff-n1236554|accessdate=15 August 2020}}</ref> He will also be the first Jewish spouse to a [[United States Vice President]].<ref name="vc-star">{{cite news |last1=Kisken |first1=Tom |title=Agoura High alumnus could become nation's first 'second gentleman' |url=https://www.vcstar.com/story/news/local/2020/08/26/who-is-kamala-harris-husband-doug-emhoff-married-agoura-high-school/3415297001/ |accessdate=27 August 2020 |publisher=Ventura County Star |date=26 August 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|date=August 13, 2020|title=Douglas Emhoff: Kamala Harris's husband and potential 'second gentleman'|language=en-gb|work=[[BBC News]]|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-53758915|access-date=August 17, 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|last=Schor|first=Elana|date=August 12, 2020|title=Harris brings Baptist, interfaith roots to Democratic ticket|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/national/religion/harris-brings-baptist-interfaith-roots-to-democratic-ticket/2020/08/12/2d319e6a-dc57-11ea-b4f1-25b762cdbbf4_story.html|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=August 17, 2020|newspaper=[[Washington Post]]|language=en}}</ref><ref name=":1" />
